description:
Grass/Garden galore! Simple/clean. Are you looking to have that NYC experience without paying the Manhattan hotel prices? Well, this private 1 bedroom apartment may be what you're looking for. 
- Private Bath & Kitchen
- Patio door in apartment opens to large backyard. During the summers, we grow fruits and veggies: Feel free to grab some!
- Bus 2 blocks away. 
- 15 minute walk or 3 minute drive/cab to 6 train which will lead you straight down to Manhattan.
- 15 minute drive to LGA airport.

-  Separate Entrance  
- We respect your privacy but are readily available to answer any of your questions or concerns.
- Wi-Fi Available
- Fire stick TV installed
- Queen size comfy bed. Mattress purchased from Sleepy's with protective covering used and washed at all times. 
-  2 additional airbeds available: (queen size and twin size) New queen size air bed. Great brand: Serta. Has firm, medium and soft setting. Twin air bed available as needed.
- newly designed by the Hernandez Family: modern feel. 
- combination of urban and suburban experience. 
- Enjoy the NYC experience yet return to a quiet rest at this home. 
- Safe. outdoor surveillance camera.

hosts.about:
I love hosting and my goal is to make your trip as smooth and comfortable as possible.
This is our family home. We are family oriented. This entire multifamily unit all comprise of family members ( husband, wife, children, grandparents, sister, niece, nephew) who are nonprofit worker/ IT workers / medical provider. We have an extra 1 bedroom apartment available for our fellow travelers. We use that space for our " Family Cave" as well when not in use. 
We love basketball, travelling, and HOME COOKING. 
Our family love the diversity aspect ( languages, food, cultures, shows)  of New York and we hope you get to experience " The City that Never Sleeps" as well. 

“I haven’t been everywhere, but it’s on my list.” – Susan Sontag

photos.caption: Faux leather couch that opens to small bed in living room
Full mirror to get dressed and ready
Part of living room. Simple and modern.
Don coqui on the water: city island's premier destination for authentic for Puerto Rican cuisine and live entertainment. Bar and lounge restaurant.
City island: many waterfront eateries. A lot of seafood !!
Havana cafe: 3151 E. Tremont Ave Bronx, NY 10461. Check out the yummy Cuban fare there. "Cojito" (coconut mojito) is our fav there. Nearby

Bay plaza is New York city's largest shopping center (780,000 square feet) with an exciting mix of over 100 department and specialty stores for your everyday shopping convenience. Some businesses such as: stop and shop, Dallas BBQ, staples, applebees, PC Richards, Raymour and flanigan, toys r us, Modells, AMC theatres, Billy Beez, five below, Macy's, JC Penny, Party city, Barnes and nobles, Starbucks, old navy, Kmart, bagel cafe..... 5 min drive. Our house overlooks the mall.

Ridge Hill Mall: Westchester, NY (7.2 miles away). Over 50 stores: Whole Foods, Legoland, lord and Taylor, restaurants, ifly (indoor sky diving), Cheesecake Factory, Apple Store, movie theater, and many more ...
City island has many waterfront restaurants
Many restaurants nearby. 5 -7 minute drive to Tosca cafe, mamajuana, Travesias ( Latin fusion) and many more! Some have live band, brunch, night life. Website has many events posted.

review.comments: This place was perfect. Ravy and Kels were amazing as well. The apartment is located near everything included the highways and any store you could need. The block is quiet and friendly. The separate entrance  makes you feel like your in your own home. I felt very safe at all hours of the night. The hosts are wonderful people gave us all the privacy we needed and were also available for any reason.  These are definitely superhost!
